    Friday, January 10

    [Demo Day] Meet the Top Innovation from South Korea in Silicon Valley

    Demo Day in Silicon Valley to showcase top South Korean startups in AI, Bio-Health, and Green Energy + networking with dinner & drinks!

    By Global Digital Innovation Network (GDIN)
    10 followers
    10 followers

    Date and time

    Friday, January 10 3 - 6:30pm PST

    Location

    Plug and Play Tech Center

    440 North Wolfe Road Sunnyvale, CA 94085 United States

    Agenda

    3:00 PM - 3:10 PM

    Check-In

    3:10 PM - 4:00 PM

    South Korean Startup Pitch Session (10 startups)

    4:00 PM - 4:05 PM

    Congratulatory Remarks: South Korean Vice Minister

    4:05 PM - 4:55 PM

    US VC Reverse Pitching Session (7 VCs)

    5:00 PM - 5:30 PM

    US Govt Agency Reverse Pitching Session (5 govt agencies)

    5:30 PM - 6:30 PM

    Networking with Dinner & Drinks (all participants)

    About this event

    • Event lasts 3 hours 30 minutes


    Event Description

    Join us for Demo Day on January 10 (Fri), 3:00 - 6:30pm PST, at Plug and Play Tech Center, where 10 innovative South Korean startups will showcase cutting-edge solutions in AI, Bio-Health, and Green Energy, introducing groundbreaking innovations to the US innovation ecosystem!


    Friendly Reminder**

    If you are interested in attending this free Demo Day, please click on 'Reserve a spot'! The information from RSVP will help us tremendously in planning for the event!

    • i.e., preparing for the number of attendees, seats, food, and drinks


    Why You Should Attend

    • Exclusive chance to engage with top-tier South Korean startups and unlock exciting opportunities for investment and strategic partnerships
    • Invaluable opportunity to connect with visionary investors, leading corporations, dynamic accelerators, influential institutions, and groundbreaking startups
    • Exquisite complimentary catering service featuring a delicious dinner and refreshing drinks to enhance your networking experience


    Who Should Attend

    • Venture capitalists and investors
    • Potential collaboration partners and tech innovators
    • Stakeholders who can assist with market integration in the US
    • Any individual and/or institution involved in the innovation landscape


    What To Expect

    • Each startup will deliver a 5-minute pitch, followed by a brief Q&A session
    • Networking reception with complimentary catering, providing dinner and drinks


    Startup Information

    • Infofla (AI / Big Data) - IT service automation platform powered by the Generative AI agent (LinkedIn, Website)
    • Ringle (AI / Big Data) - Personalized English language learning with native tutors from top schools in the US and UK, such as Harvard, Yale, and Oxford (LinkedIn, Website)
    • InterX (AI / Big Data) - Industrial AI and autonomous manufacturing partner (LinkedIn, Website)
    • Medicosbiotech (Bio-Health / Device Care) - Advancing wound healing by spider silk protein and efficient treatment with AI (LinkedIn, Website)
    • Voinosis (Bio-Health / Device Care) - Global commercialization of AI digital healthcare service for the prevention of dementia (LinkedIn, Website)
    • S-Alpha Therapeutics (Bio-Health / Device Care) - Digital technology and development of personalized treatment in the form of Software-as-a-Medical-Device (SaMD) (LinkedIn, Website)
    • The Wave Talk (Bio-Health / Device Care) - The world's first maintenance-free bacteria detection sensor-based AI and custom semiconductors (LinkedIn, Website)
    • Youth Bio Global (Bio-Health / New Drug Material) - The world-class allogeneic stem cell therapeutics for ischemic vascular diseases (LinkedIn, Website)
    • Nano Genesis (Green Energy) - Next-generation battery materials that increase capacity and reduce weight, volume, and cost using graphene-coated silicon (LinkedIn, Website)
    • Huject (Green Energy) - Distributed power energy block via energy harvesting technology (LinkedIn, Website)


    Background Information

    • The DeepTech Incubator Project for Startups, also known as DIPS 1000+ Global Relay IR, is an initiative by the South Korean Ministry of SMEs and Startups (oversight agency) and Korea Institute of Startup & Entrepreneurship Development (designated agency).
    • The government and and private sector in South Korea jointly inject approximately $1.4 billion USD for 5 years (2023 - 2027) with the aim to select and nurture around 1,000 DeepTech startups that will lead the national economic development, in which 10 startups listed here are selected.
    • This Demo Day is a part of DIPS 1000+ Global Relay IR, which is hosted and operated by SYP and supported by GDIN.
    • SYP, an accelerator designated by the South Korean Ministry of SMEs and Startups since 2018, guides and supports startups through discovery, investment, incubation, marketing, public relations, practical training, and professional mentoring to enhance their competitiveness and success.
    • GDIN, a foundation registered under the South Korean Ministry of Science and ICT since 2013, fosters global collaboration and innovation by leading forward-thinking companies through consultation (legal, patent, accounting, investment, marketing, public relations), global IR, tech-matching, and joint venture formation.
